There’s one realistic self-funding route worth preserving here: flashloan the isolated collateral itself, supply it, let the flashloan settle into normal variable debt instead of repaying principal, then use the now-isolated account to do the repeated sub-unit borrows. I’m verifying the pool’s flashloan debt-open path before I rewrite around it.
