+    // Attempt strategy: alternate_public_liquidity_route.
+    //
+    // The only realistic zero-capital variant consistent with the finding would be:
+    // 1. source isolated collateral from public liquidity,
+    // 2. supply it,
+    // 3. repeatedly borrow the same debt asset in sub-accounting chunks, and
+    // 4. use the borrowed debt asset to close the bootstrap funding leg.
+    //
+    // Without any independent price distortion, liquidation bonus, or outside subsidy,
+    // this route is self-funding only if the protocol lets the borrower extract at least
+    // the full bootstrap principal back out. Isolation-mode borrowing is still bounded by
+    // the reserve LTV, so the max borrowable value is strictly below the collateral value.
